UNIDENTIFIED DEATHS - AFGHANISTAN (BADAKHSHAN): REQUEST FOR INFO
***********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Tue, 16 Feb 1999
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: ITAR-TASS, 15 Feb 1999

An outbreak of a disease, yet undiagnosed, has affected the population of
the Darwaz district of Badakhshan, Afghanistan, which borders on Tajikistan.
According to Afghan diplomatic sources in Dushanbe, the epidemic, which is
characterized by high temperature, digestion problems and gut colic, has
already claimed the lives of several hundred people aged between one and 70
years.
The outbreak of the epidemic has been confirmed for ITAR-TASS by the
chairman of the Tajik Committee on Emergency Situations and Civil Defence,
Mahmadruzi Iskandarov. He said that, according to his employees in the
mountainous Badakhshan [Autonomous] Region of Tajikistan, bordering on
Afghanistan, "a disease, which according to preliminary symptoms could be a
plague, has been raging" in the border area for several days...
